## Upstream Kubernetes vs Distribution

| Feature      | Upstream K8s | K8 Distribution |
| ------------ | ------------ | --------------- |
| Installation | Manual       | Automated       |
| Networking   | You choose   | Preconfigured   |
| Storage      | You add      | Included        |
| Security     | DIY          | Built-in        |
| Support      | Community    | Vendor support  |

---

## Which one should **you** focus on (DevOps learning path)

Since youâ€™re learning DevOps as a beginner, I strongly recommend:

### âœ… Step-by-step path

1. **Minikube** â†’ understand basics (pods, services, deployments)
2. **K3s** â†’ real-world lightweight cluster
3. **EKS / GKE** â†’ production-grade Kubernetes
4. **Rancher / OpenShift** â†’ enterprise exposure

> This mirrors how real DevOps engineers grow in production environments.

